        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[Genu Berlo]]></title>
            <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://the-grid-user-content.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/e4a47284-766c-4f0f-bec4-65855e670b19.jpg">,<h1>Genu Berlo</h1>,<p>American - born Romanian - working in New York, Bucuresti and Ghirdoveni</p>,<p>In painting, installation, land art and sculpture I reflect on ideas such as Magnetic Body Space Interaction, Awareness Field and Layers, Expressions and Fractality of Body and Mind, Architectural nesting of the Body. A recurring theme in my work is also the relationship between language and space, mental and physical. In exploring Awareness states, I like using patterns and images of ancient and archaic source. I also experiment with “<strong>non-action painting</strong>” which I call a state of mind and body similar to Zen, where form and color are not important, yet they are a direct result of this state, almost compulsive, and it is significant to self. I worked as a designer architect in New York City architectural firms, including Skidmore, Owings and Merrill, Dan Ionescu Architects, Peix and Marchetti Architects, Mihai Radu Architects.</p>,<p>Education: Continuing Education in Fine Arts - Fashion Institute of Technology of NYC 2003; Bachelors in Architecture - University of Bucharest 2001; Bachelors in Math - University of Bucharest 1997</p>]]></description>
            <link>http://berlo.net/genu-berlo/index.html</link>
            <guid isPermaLink="false">95c659e9-76dc-427b-a5a1-c6d1b5dfd20f</guid>
            <pubDate>Tue, 28 Mar 2017 15:31:28 GMT</pubDate>
        </item>
